Post.create({title:"Better View Than Empire State", image:"http://gaees.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/rockefeller-center-tree-2014.jpg", content:" The Empire State Building may be the more iconic of these two skyscrapers, but the view from the top of the Rockefeller just can't be beat! You get to look right over Central Park and you get some unobstructed views (no wire fences) on some of its multistage lookouts. A little part of me just liked being here because of the iconic poster of workers on the beam. The good news for geeks like me is you get to take your very own picture like this (inside). If you have the time to scale two skyscrapers - go here! And it is worth a consideration over the Empire State Building even if you don't!", vote_up: 0, vote_down: 0, user_id: 1, location_id: 30, category_id: 2 })
